:"1337","1359":"1359","1356":"1356","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1332":"1332","1320":"1320","about 1320":"omkring 1320","1417":"1417","1328":"1328","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1320–1 February 1359":"circa 1320–1 februari 1359","1320–1359":"1320–1359","1320–1384":"1320–1384","1332–1417":"1332–1417","1349–1389":"1349–1389","1286–1349":"1286–1349","16 May 1349":"16 mei 1349","1 February 1359":"1 februari 1359","1286":"1286","1384":"1384","4 June 1349":"4 juni 1349","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1359":"1359","1356":"1356","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1332":"1332","1320":"1320","about 1320":"circa 1320","1417":"1417","1328":"1328","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1320–1 February 1359":"about 1320–1 February 1359","1320–1359":"1320–1359","1320–1384":"1320–1384","1332–1417":"1332–1417","1349–1389":"1349–1389","1286–1349":"1286–1349","16 May 1349":"16 May 1349","1 February 1359":"1 February 1359","1286":"1286","1384":"1384","4 June 1349":"4 June 1349","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1359":"1359","1356":"1356","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1332":"1332","1320":"1320","about 1320":"about 1320","1417":"1417","1328":"1328","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Harley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from either of two places called Harley (Shropshire, Yorkshire). The Shropshire placename derives from Old English <i>hær</i> ‘rock, heap of stones’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. The Yorkshire placename derives from Old English <i>hara</i> ‘hare’ or <i>hær</i> + <i>hlāw</i> ‘mound, hill’, later replaced by <i>lēah</i>.","Irish (Donegal): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hEarghaile</b> ‘descendant of <i>Earghal</i>’, a variant of the personal name <i>Fearghal</i> without the initial <i>F-</i>. This name has also become   Herley   and   Hurley  . Compare   Arrell   and   Harrell  .","Scottish (Fife): habitational name from any of several places called Harlaw in Midlothian, Peeblesshire, and Berwickshire, named in Older Scots with <i>hare</i> ‘gray’ + <i>law</i> ‘hill’."],"variants":[{"name":"Herley","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Art, Cormac.","Irish: variant of   Hurley  , probably via   Herlihy  .","English: variant of   Harley   or   Hurley  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":8,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":17,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert De Harley was born about 1320, in Harley, Shropshire, England, his father, Sir Robert Harley, was 35 and his mother, Margaret de Brampton, was 35. He married Joan Corbet in 1356, in Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 1 February 1359, at the age of 40."},"et":{"about 1320–1 February 1359":"umbes 1320–1. veebruar 1359","1320–1359":"1320–1359","1320–1384":"1320–1384","1332–1417":"1332–1417","1349–1389":"1349–1389","1286–1349":"1286–1349","16 May 1349":"16. mai 1349","1 February 1359":"1. veebruar 1359","1286":"1286","1384":"1384","4 June 1349":"4. juuni 1349","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1359":"1359","1356":"1356","1389